        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 2:33PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 232 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Haddam, or near Chester, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Chester and East Haddam around 240 PM EDT.
Colchester around 250 PM EDT.
Salem around 300 PM EDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter.

Heavy rain is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
